A scientist has obtained two random samples: $X_1, X_2, ..., X_n \stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim}$ ~ Exp($\theta$), independently of $Y_1, Y_2, ..., Y_m \stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim}$ Exp(k$\theta$), where $\theta \geq 0$ is the (unknown) mean of the distribution and k is some known positive number. We want to find the estimator which is a weighted average of the two estimators. $T_1 = a\hat{\theta_1} + (1-a)\hat{\theta_2}$ where the constant a($0 \leq a \leq 1$) is chosen to minimize Var($T_1$). Find a. Output your answer in one fraction or number. Show no work.
